posts.post_content:
@niceguygreensboro  
[Crosis's Attendant](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Crosis's Attendant).  

@Shadoflaam  
Not really. [Snapcaster](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Snapcaster) is probably overall better, but this card allows you to reuse *two* cards instead of one. Instead of an extra use, [snapcaster](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=snapcaster) gives you a 2/1, flash, and the ability to use instants out of the graveyard.  

@lorendorky  
Only problem is that if you flashback [Surreal Memoir](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Surreal Memoir), you don't get the rebound. Rebound only works when you cast it from your hand (otherwise it would rebound forever lol).  

@dybeck  
It seems like it's extremely narrow, and it's definitely more narrow than other cards that give flash back to anything ([snapcaster mage](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=snapcaster mage)), but sorceries are literally half of the different types of cards that can even *have* flashback.
